1 and maintain school gardens to increase the time teachers allocate to
2 teaching science, technology, engineering and mathematics; and
3 (4) Development and implementation of a food safety plan
4 designed to ensure that food grown in a school garden is properly
5 handled and safe to sell and consume;
6 (b) Pay for any travel expenses associated with the attendance of
7 a teacher at any training or conference relating to school gardens;
8 and
9 (c) Pay for the costs of a conference regarding school gardens
10 held in this State.
11 5. As used in this section:
12 (a) “Public school” has the meaning ascribed to it in
13 NRS 385.007.
14 (b) “School garden” includes, without limitation, a hydroponic
15 garden.
16 Sec. 2. Upon acceptance of the money allocated pursuant to
17 section 1 of this act, a nonprofit organization agrees to:
18 1. Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
19 Committee on or before October 1, 2026, that describes each
20 expenditure made from the money allocated pursuant to section 1 of
21 this act from the date on which the money was received by the
22 nonprofit organization through June 30, 2026;
23 2. Prepare and transmit a final report to the Interim Finance
24 Committee on or before October 1, 2027, that describes each
25 expenditure made from the money allocated pursuant to section 1 of
26 this act from the date on which the money was received by the
27 nonprofit organization through June 30, 2027; and
28 3. Upon request of the Legislative Commission, make available
29 to the Legislative Auditor any of the books, accounts, claims,
30 reports, vouchers or other records of information, confidential or
31 otherwise, of the nonprofit organization, regardless of their form or
32 location, that the Legislative Auditor deems necessary to conduct an
33 audit of the use of the money allocated pursuant to section 1 of this
34 act.
35 Sec. 3. Any balance of the sums appropriated by section 1 of
36 this act remaining at the end of the respective fiscal years must not
37 be committed for expenditure after June 30 of the respective fiscal
38 years by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
39 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
40 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
41 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
42 September 18, 2026, and September 17, 2027, respectively, by
43 either the entity to which the money was appropriated or the entity
44 to which the money was subsequently granted or transferred, and
